mutabor_interval mutabor::hidden::mutabor_get_interval_from_pitch ( double  pitch)
inline

Convert an interval from half tone based pitch according to MIDI pitch numbers.

The microtonal part can be given in the double value.

Parameter
intervala double value that represents the interval. a semitone is represented as 1.00, and an octave as 12.00
Rückgabe
interval in the internal representation of Mutabor.
Zu beachten
The resulting interval is always a valid non-nil interval.

Add the distance of t1 - t2 to offset.

This function transfers the interval between two tones to two other tones.

Parameter
offsetnew base tone
t1old tone
t2old base tone
Rückgabe
offset + (t1 - t2)

1589  if (YYMAXDEPTH <= yystacksize)

1604 # undef YYSTACK_RELOCATE

1607  }

1643

3170 yyabortlab:
3171  yyresult = 1;
3172  goto yyreturn;
3173 
3174 #if !defined yyoverflow || YYERROR_VERBOSE
3175 /*-------------------------------------------------.
3176 | yyexhaustedlab -- memory exhaustion comes here. |
3177 `-------------------------------------------------*/
3178 yyexhaustedlab:
3179  yyerror (&yylloc, box, YY_("memory exhausted"));
3180  yyresult = 2;
3181  /* Fall through. */
3182 #endif
3183 
3184 yyreturn:
3185  if (yychar != YYEMPTY)
3186  {
3187  /* Make sure we have latest lookahead translation. See comments at
3188  user semantic actions for why this is necessary. */
3189  yytoken = YYTRANSLATE (yychar);
3190  yydestruct ("Cleanup: discarding lookahead",
3191  yytoken, &yylval, &yylloc, box);
3192  }
3193  /* Do not reclaim the symbols of the rule whose action triggered
3194  this YYABORT or YYACCEPT. */
3195  YYPOPSTACK (yylen);
3196  YY_STACK_PRINT (yyss, yyssp);
3197  while (yyssp != yyss)
3198  {
3199  yydestruct ("Cleanup: popping",
3200  yystos[*yyssp], yyvsp, yylsp, box);
3201  YYPOPSTACK (1);
3202  }
3203 #ifndef yyoverflow
3204  if (yyss != yyssa)
3205  YYSTACK_FREE (yyss);
3206 #endif
3207 #if YYERROR_VERBOSE
3208  if (yymsg != yymsgbuf)
3209  YYSTACK_FREE (yymsg);
3210 #endif
3211  return yyresult;
3212 }
